article_title: Barack Obama, Benjamin Netanyahu Clash on Possible Iran Nuclear Deal
article_text:
President Barack Obama said the U.S. and other world powers have offered Tehran “an extraordinarily reasonable” nuclear deal after efforts during the past week to move the negotiations forward and shore up support among Arab and European allies.

But Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said an agreement would allow Iran to soon have “many,...

twitter.description: President Obama took to the airwaves to defend the ongoing talks aimed at curtailing Iran’s ability to produce nuclear arms. However, Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu and some U.S. lawmakers fear the deal won’t go far enough.
